Distribution . Turkey and Greece are clearly the centers of distribution in the sense that the majority of species is largely or entirely restricted to Turkey and Greece , in particular southern Turkey and Crete. Three widespread species extend the distribution of the genus toward eastern Central Europe (
H. forskali
), toward the area around the eastern Black Sea (
H. longipes
), and toward the Levante (
H. cecconii
) ( Fig. 5 ). Previous records from the Adriatic Coast, Iraq , and Turkmenistan are very probably based on misidentifications (see Distribution section in the redescription of
H. forskali
).
